Lewis Capaldi is a pretty big deal in the world of music. The 23-year-old Scotsman may have only brought out one album so far – his debut, ‘Divinely Uninspired to a Hellish Extent’ – but he’s already breaking world records left, right and centre in a hugely impressive career. After such an incredible 2019, life come to a bit of a halt for Lewis during the global pandemic in 2020, but the singer has now revealed he will release his second album in 2021, admitting he’s quitting social media to work on it. Taking to Twitter to confirm the news, Lewis released a lengthy statement which read, ‘Honestly been the most incredible few years and it means the world to have the support of all of you. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! ‘Going to f–k off for a wee bit now to crack on and finish the second album. Wont be using any social media so you’1ll all have to make do without me talking s—e and constantly trying to take your money by flogging you something.’ He added, ‘Hope you all had a lovely Christmas and New Year and I’ll see you big lovely b——s later in the year with some new music that I imagine will be universally panned by critics and will fail to be as commercially successful as my last outing. Another Proposed Nude Party Aborted, To Be Investigated Ekene Dili Chukwu’s Son Dies Of COVID-19 In Lagos ‘Thus spelling the beginning of the end of the 15 minutes of fame that quite frankly, I never deserved in the first place. ‘IT’S ALL VERY EXCITING. LOVE YOU, STAY SAFE AND BYE FOR NOW’. (sic) SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION